### Art. 1(1) COURSES

Italian and international students who meet the financial and merit requirements set out in the following articles 6 (general requirements), 9 (first years), 15 (subsequent years), 24 (PhDs and specialisation schools), 29 (students with disabilities) and 30 and 31 (international students), enrolled for the academic year 2025/26 at Piedmont universities identified in the following paragraph, may apply for the scholarship and, if non-resident, the accommodation service in the following types of courses:

- 1. bachelor’s degree;
- 2. single-cycle master's degree;
- 3. master's degree (Ministerial Decree 270/04);
- 4. PhD courses (Legislative Decree 210/98) who do not benefit from the scholarship1P;
- 5. specialisation schools of at least two years' duration, excluding medical schools under Legislative Decree 368/1999. Students enrolled at PhD courses or specialisation schools can apply only for scholarship The scholarships relate to the academic year 2025/26. With regard to students enrolled in specialisation schools, scholarships may be granted to those with active enrolment in the relevant academic year of the related school2.


With regard to scholarships awarded to students enrolled in the additional semester, in addition to the merit and income requirements, enrolment in the current academic year at the time of the application is sufficient, as stipulated in art. 3(5) of Ministerial Decree 1320/2021. Therefore, EDISU (Regional Agency for the Right to Education) will not proceed with the verification of their enrolment for the 2025/26 academic year. Students graduating in September 2025 will not be able to apply for a scholarship for the additional semester but only for the degree award if they meet the requirements set out in Section V below.

Students enrolled at the University of Turin in the joint degrees EAP - Economic Analysis and Policy, LM (MASTER’S DEGREE (Master’s Degree))-56, or EISD - Economics of Innovation for Sustainable Development, LM-56 may participate in this notice of competition, provided that they have not been awarded scholarships granted by the French study support (on the basis of merit and income) or other scholarships granted for similar purposes by the European Community (e.g. Erasmus Mundus Joint Master Degree). If these students only wish to access the canteen service at a reduced cost, they must submit an application in accordance with the Regulations for the Canteen Service, academic year 2025/26.

Students enrolled at the Polytechnic University of Turin in the Master's Degree Course in Energy and Nuclear Engineering (Turin), pathway SELECT - Environomical Pathways for Sustainable Energy Systems - EIT Joint Programme may participate in this notice of competition, provided they have not been awarded other scholarships granted for similar purposes by the European Community (e.g. Erasmus Mundus Joint Master Degree). If these students only wish to access the canteen service at a reduced cost, they must submit an application in accordance with the Regulations for the Canteen Service, academic year 2025/26.

Students enrolled in Double Degrees or in international programmes within the Erasmus Mundus Joint Master's initiative whose primary enrolment is at an extended university (lead university) are not eligible to apply for an EDISU scholarship. However, these students will be able to access the canteen at a reduced cost (first bracket) as incoming foreign/exchange students. The university will send EDISU the list of these students they year they attend in Turin, so they do not have to register on EDISU's online services.

UPDATE Art. 9 sets out specific provisions for students attending the “filter semester” of medicina e chirurgia, medicina veterinaria e Odontoiatria e protesi dentaria courses.

### Art. 6 para. 1.7 REGISTERED COHABITATION PURSUANT TO ART. 5 OF PRESIDENTIAL DECREE 223/89

|Definition of registered cohabitation: a group of persons normally cohabiting for religious, care, military or punishment reasons and having their residence at the same address (religious institution, nursing home, barracks, prison, etc.).|
|---|


In all cases where students meet the requirements of art. 5 of Presidential Decree 223/89, they may apply to have the ISEE Universitario certificate in registered cohabitation issued by presenting appropriate documentation proving their status to the CAAF and, subsequently, to EDISU Piemonte. The categories envisaged for registered cohabitation are:

- • belonging to a religious order;
- • military;
- • host communities;
- • subjected to detention.


In the event that the student who is in a registered cohabitation (military, host community, or subject to detention) is “MARRIED”, they must refer to the household of their spouse and any children, as described in section 1.4 above, for the purpose of preparing the ISEE Universitario certificate. If the applicant and their minor child live in the registered cohabitation, the latter must be considered a member of the parent's household (see the document “List of certifications to be attached to the application for students with a student-only household, international protection seekers and the disabled” available in the “Scholarships > attachments” section of the EDISU website).

### Art. 13(6) MERIT REQUIREMENTS FOR MAINTAINING ELIGIBILITY

Eligible students who are not successful in the final scholarship ranking may maintain their eligibility, and with it their exemption from paying tuition fees in accordance with their University's Fee Regulations, only if they obtain at least 20 credits (11 if enrolled part-time) by 30 November 2026. These credits must also be duly registered by your University Student Administrative Office on or before 30 November 2026.

The following may NOT be counted in the sum of credits:

- 1. credits from unfulfilled academic requirements;
- 2. credits of modules in progress that require further work for the final grade;
- 3. credits from individual modules that are not recognised;
- 4. excess credits;
- 5. credits validated by overseas study;
- 6. credits from the 24-credit/60-credit course for teacher training. Please also note that the bonus can only be used to apply as a subsequent year; therefore, it CANNOT be used for first-year merit achievement.


The 18 credits obtained for access to the courses referred to in Ministerial Decree 418 of 30 May 2025 are valid for obtaining the 20 credits required for the second instalment of the scholarship.

